fix: replace dark-only HSL tokens with theme-aware CSS vars in globals.css

Root cause identified: globals.css had two :root blocks. The first
defined --surface-elevated, --surface-secondary, --text-primary-hsl,
--text-muted-hsl etc as always-dark navy values (designed for dark
mode only). The dashboard hero CSS classes used these dark-only tokens,
causing dark backgrounds in light mode with inherited black page text
sitting on top — invisible text across all sections.

Classes fixed (all now use theme-aware tokens):
- .dashboard-hero:      --bg-card instead of hsl(--surface-elevated)
- .hero-stat-card:      --bg-hover instead of hsl(--surface-secondary)
- .hero-stat-value:     explicit color: var(--text-primary)
- .hero-label:          --text-muted instead of hsl(--text-muted-hsl)
- .hero-sub:            --text-muted instead of hsl(--text-muted-hsl)
- .hero-progress-label: --text-muted instead of hsl(--text-muted-hsl)
- .hero-progress-val:   --text-primary instead of hsl(--text-primary-hsl)
- .hero-progress-track: --bg-hover instead of hsl(--surface-secondary)
- .hero-progress-bar:   --text-primary instead of hsl(--text-primary-hsl)
- .transaction-row:     --bg-hover instead of hsl(--surface-secondary)
- .skeleton-row/lines:  --bg-hover instead of rgba(255,255,255,0.05)
- .balance-text:        --text-primary instead of hsl(--text-primary-hsl)
- .mobile-nav-item:     --text-muted/primary instead of HSL tokens
- .mobile-nav:          --border and color-mix bg instead of HSL tokens

Result: all hero panels, transaction rows, skeleton loaders, and the
balance text now correctly adapt between light and dark themes. Text
is always readable regardless of the active theme.
